# Bidding Challenge: "Trinity Fusion" Strategy

We are evolving the strategy to **Phase 8: Trinity Fusion**. After verifying that dataset correction fixed the regression (v15 OOF 0.46), we identified that combining v12's Bayesian Market Estimates with v15's Granular Namazani Features is the path to < 0.30 RMSLE.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Pivot to Fusion**: [v15](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/bidding_v15_total_domination.py#65-155) proved that the dataset is fixed (0.45 public score), but `v12` remains superior (0.39) due to its [market_est](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/bidding_v14_trinity_fix.py#76-107) logic. We are now fusing both.
> **Validation Hardening**: We will use 10-fold `StratifiedGroupKFold` to ensure the most robust local CV possible.

## Proposed Changes

### Model Training

#### [NEW] [bidding_v16_trinity_fusion.py](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/bidding_v16_trinity_fusion.py)
1. **Hybrid Feature Engineering**:
   - **From v12**: [get_leak_free_estimates](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/bidding_v12_overdrive.py#49-72) (Bayesian priors on item-level unit prices).
   - **From v15**: [aggregate_namazani](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/S6E1_Phase7_TotalDomination.py#132-151) (Count/Category/Quantity aggregations), [apply_macro_features](file:///home/kizabgd/Desktop/Istrazivanje/construction_bidding/bidding_v15_total_domination.py#56-64) (Inflation + Temporal Lag), and `Contractor Clustering`.
